// Cortex-M3 + 64 KB SRAM / 512 KB flash, plus a RAM-mapped DMA descriptor +
// coherency register window for the dma-own ownership driver content-gate. The
// gate asserts the exact effects the DRIVER pokes THROUGH the trusted gust:hal DMA
// seam (descriptor program ch/len, coherency barrier op) at each ownership handoff,
// plus the Kani-proven ownership round-trip (Wasm->Dma->Wasm, barrier-by-
// construction, abort-never-ownerless) — on a plain memory region, deterministic,
// no dependence on a Renode DMA-controller peripheral model.
cpu: CPU.CortexM @ sysbus
    cpuType: "cortex-m3"
    nvic: nvic
nvic: IRQControllers.NVIC @ sysbus 0xE000E000
    -> cpu@0
flash: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x0
    size: 0x80000
sram: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x20000000
    size: 0x10000
// DMA descriptor + coherency register window (real STM32F1 DMA1 base, 0x40020000)
// as plain memory — the driver's program/barrier seam writes read back. Ends at
// 0x40020400, below RCC (0x40021000) and USART1 (0x40013800) — no overlap.
dma: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x40020000
    size: 0x400
usart1: UART.STM32_UART @ sysbus <0x40013800, +0x100>
    -> nvic@37
